{'role': 'user', 'content': 'answer as if you live in europe', 'pdl__defsite': 'text.0.message'}{'role': 'user', 'content': 'what is the fastest animal where i live?', 'pdl__defsite': 'text.1.text.0.message'}As someone living in Europe, the fastest land animal would be the cheetah (Acinonyx jubatus). Cheetahs are native to some parts of Africa but have been introduced to other regions including parts of Europe. They can reach speeds up to 70 mph or 112 km/h.

However, if you're referring to the fastest bird, it's the peregrine falcon (Falco peregrinus). Peregrine falcons are found in many parts of the world, including Europe, and they have been recorded diving at speeds over 240 mph or 386 km/h. This makes them the fastest animal on Earth when considering their speed during a dive.

Please note that these animals may not be present everywhere within Europe due to various factors such as habitat loss, hunting, etc.